<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="110" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1014,1365]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">
Although often treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Hoese et al. (2015)" authorityName="Hoese" authorityYear="2015" box="[597,749,1050,1076]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[597,749,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Glossogobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Hoese 
<emphasis box="[839,888,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">et al</emphasis>
. (2015) provided detailed morphological reasons for recognising the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="110" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,1014,1365]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authority="Cantor, 1849" authorityName="Cantor" authorityYear="1849" box="[151,491,1122,1148]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sublitus">
<emphasis box="[151,329,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Gobius sublitus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cantor, T. E." box="[340,491,1122,1148]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" pagination="983 - 1443" refId="ref26823" refString="Cantor, T. E. (1849) Catalogue of Malayan fishes. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, 18 (2), 983 - 1443." type="journal article" year="1849">Cantor, 1849</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[886,992,1122,1148]" name="Malaysia" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1060,1158,1122,1148]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">holotype</typeStatus>
is a varnished skin and clearly has a lappet over the eye and a broad gill opening indicating 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1936" box="[951,1122,1158,1184]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Psammogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[951,1122,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Psammogobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two species are being confused under the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[441,741,1194,1220]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Psammogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="biocellatus">
<emphasis box="[441,741,1194,1220]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Psammogobius biocellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[755,904,1194,1220]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Psammogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="biocellatus">
<emphasis box="[755,904,1194,1220]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">P. biocellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with opercular scales and fully scaled predorsal and a second species without opercular scales and reduced predorsal scales. The second species probably has a name, but we have not examined sufficient type material to be sure of the appropriate name. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1837" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Psammogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="biocellatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Psammogobius biocellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the Indian Ocean and western Pacific, but the second species is only known from the western and central Pacific.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
